Granting the Z3 results and any formal repair, the slide from synchronicity to singularity still fails on three independent grounds.

h10: Centrality is not uniqueness. A repaired Path A (fixed G; Royal Purple = intense traversal) still lacks an isomorphism-invariant rule that singles out exactly one node. To be scientific, define a graph-internal selector U that:
- Takes an unlabeled DAG G and returns a single v* or “none.”
- Is invariant under graph isomorphisms.
- Does not depend on biographical labels.
A necessary condition is that v* occupy a unique automorphism orbit in G. Most centrality scores (degree, betweenness, eigenvector, k-core) do not uniquely select a single node in the presence of graph symmetries; adding ad hoc tie-breakers via real-world labels violates invariance. Under Path B (sequence {Gi}), you must also exhibit an isomorphism-invariant identity map across slices that preserves uniqueness over time. Absent U, “I am the singularity” is non-falsifiable.

h11: Eponymic identification is a genetic fallacy. Scientific units are fixed by operational invariants, not authorship. Provide an operationalization of BIT that any lab can reproduce independent of the proponent’s identity, e.g.:
- A psychophysical protocol that estimates the minimal discriminable unit of conscious difference under pre-registered tasks (2AFC, rivalry, masking) with cross-lab reliability.
- Or an information-theoretic quantity tied to measurable neural or behavioral data with specified estimators and error bars.
Until then, “BIT = Briana” is rhetoric, not metrology.

h12: Pre-register the reference class and correct for multiplicity. Jung’s synchronicity is observer-indexed; it cannot ground objective uniqueness. Hájek’s reference-class problem applies: “uniquely positioned” is meaningless without R. Specify R (e.g., all living researchers eligible to write a 2026 theory of consciousness), pre-register the feature list F before looking, and report multiplicity-corrected likelihoods P(≥1 member of R matches F). With features like equinox birth (~0.5%), Mula (~3.7%), Cambridge birth, named-parent, specific course enrollment, plus countless unreported flex degrees, the Texas sharpshooter effect dominates; at global population scale, we expect many near-matches by chance.

Jung’s warning stands: identifying the ego with archetypal contents (“I am the Singularity”) is inflation, not discovery. If Path A/B removes ontic creation, only autobiographical pattern-mining remains—precisely the case Jung counseled to de-personalize.

